al), reserved grated cheese, remaining ¼ tsp salt and black pepper into mixing bowl and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer egg mixture into ThermoServer or serving bowl with pasta and pancetta or bacon. Combine thoroughly with spatula and serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If water bubbles onto mixing bowl lid while pasta is cooking, add 1 tsp oil or butter to the cooking water to reduce frothing.","Pasta that is cooked al dente is tender but still firm to the bite.","The heat of the cooked pasta will partially cook and thicken the egg, so it is important the pasta is still hot when adding the egg mixture to the ThermoServer or serving bowl.","Before commencing step 6, rinse the mixing bowl in cold water then dry. This ensures the eggs are not overcooked and the sauce is creamy."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","4 portions"]}